Before you even purchase the fruit, you’ll need a “blueprint” to help you decide what kind of fruit to purchase, how much, and the overall design scope. Decide how you will present the fruit. You could lay out the heart-shaped fruit on a platter or you could line hearts up on a wooden skewer. Additionally, you could “mix and match” fruit shapes (i.e. cut out a heart shape inside a slice of watermelon and then replace the cut space with a heart that was cut from a mango). {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/99/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/9/99/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Select your serving bowl or platter. The size will dictate the amount of room your arrangement will take up on the table or display. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/7/7a/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-1Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Avoid mushy (or overly ripe) fruit. That way, the fruit will taste better. Make sure that when you hold the fruit in your hands, you can gently squeeze it so it doesn’t dent. Examine fruit for molding or browning. Even though you may not be using the rind or external section of the fruit, browning may indicate that the flesh may be compromised. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/f/fc/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet1.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet1.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
</p><p><br />
</p></div>"}

Consider choosing fruit that is in season. Purchasing fruit is not only for freshness, but fruit that is in season will save you a good chunk of money. {"smallUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1d/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-459px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","bigUrl":"https://www.wikihow.com/images/thumb/1/1d/Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet2.jpg/v4-759px-Make-Heart-Shaped-Fruit-Designs-Step-3Bullet2.jpg","smallWidth":460,"smallHeight":306,"bigWidth":760,"bigHeight":506.31868131868134,"licensing":"<div class="mw-parser-output"><p>License: <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-sa/3.0/">Creative Commons</a><br>
